MBOMBELA – President Cyril Ramaphosa said he will work with the leadership in the North West Province to resolve current political issues there. The president will be meeting with the provincial ANC and the embattled premier Supra Mahumapelo next week. Ramaphosa was speaking in Mbombela, Mpumalanga on Saturday during one of his trademark morning walks. WATCH: ANC Vets call on Cyril Ramaphosa to act against Supra He will be attending the University of Mpumalanga's third graduation ceremony later. ANC President Cde @CyrilRamaphosa chats to members of the media subsequent to this morning’s walk. pic.twitter.com/jtJjdeB3cv “The ANC is a living organisation. We will always have problems, challenges, solutions, successes and forward movement. We always find the ANC way to resolve issues” ANC President Cde @CyrilRamaphosa pic.twitter.com/7PPl3kTlEW “Let us not lose hope. Let us focus ourselves on everything that is positive...” Comrade President Ramaphosa addresses walkers on conclusion of this morning’s walk pic.twitter.com/o3qrCyuC3V eNCA